01:25:47.000 --> 01:25:55.000
As I said, these two aspects are constantly present in the strategy of various companies.

01:25:55.000 --> 01:26:07.000
The financial aspect is often considered as a priority for businesses focused on re-sales.

01:26:07.000 --> 01:26:15.000
In a traditional situation, the initiative group of managers can turn to the board of directors

01:26:15.000 --> 01:26:23.000
to include any project in the investment budget, focusing on the management aspect, i.e. the growth of sales volume.

01:26:23.000 --> 01:26:33.000
At the same time, the board of directors can correct this application and say, for example,

01:26:33.000 --> 01:26:37.000
that they are ready to allocate 10 million dollars for the implementation of the project,

01:26:37.000 --> 01:26:45.000
and they agree that the net profit from the results of this project will be 3 million dollars per year.

01:26:45.000 --> 01:26:54.000
In addition, they can ensure that the market value of the new business, which will be allocated to a separate company,

01:26:54.000 --> 01:26:59.000
will cost about 20 million dollars per year.

01:26:59.000 --> 01:27:05.000
This is a more complex task, primarily from an organizational point of view,

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:12.000
but for shareholders, the financial aspect can be the first priority, rather than the management aspect.

01:27:13.000 --> 01:27:22.000
The capital profit of a company is represented by the formula as a ratio of the profit divided by the size of the capital itself

01:27:22.000 --> 01:27:32.000
minus the dividends divided by the size of the capital itself plus the additional share release divided by the size of the capital itself.

01:27:33.000 --> 01:27:44.000
At the same time, the profitability of the capital itself is calculated as the division of the profit by the total amount of assets

01:27:44.000 --> 01:27:54.000
or the cost of the property complex that is at the disposal of the company plus the difference in the ratio of the profit to the assets

01:27:54.000 --> 01:28:02.000
for the withdrawal of interest that must be paid for the maintenance of the borrowed capital to the increase of the borrowed capital,

01:28:02.000 --> 01:28:06.000
all this multiplied by the borrowed capital.

01:28:06.000 --> 01:28:20.000
The profitability of the assets in the company is calculated as the profit in relation to the revenue multiplied by the revenue divided by the amount of assets,

01:28:20.000 --> 01:28:29.000
which can be expanded and represented by the formula of profitability of sales multiplied by the turnover of assets.

01:28:29.000 --> 01:28:35.000
As for the main task that is set before the managers in the complex,

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:41.000
